'''--- Cargo.toml ---
[package]
name = "near_postcards"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2018"

[lib]
crate-type = ["cdylib", "rlib"]

[dependencies]
near-sdk = "4.0.0-pre.7"
chrono = "0.4.13"

[profile.release]
codegen-units = 1
opt-level = "z"
lto = true
debug = false
panic = "abort"
overflow-checks = true

'''--- README.md ---
<a href="https://pcards.near.page" target="_blank">pcards.near.page</a>, <a href="https://pcards.testnet.page" target="_blank">pcards.testnet.page</a><br />

## Introduction
Near Postcards dApp is an example of a fully decentralized Near protocol service that stores all data directly on the blockchain itself, including design templates and web interface.

Also, the service is an example of integrating any application into an official wallet through the Collectibles tab. Just open a postcard image in a new browser tab and you will be redirected to the project page.

In this way, you can significantly improve the usability of your application.

### Usage

The service provides the ability to send NFT images simulating paper postcards with a postage stamp with the flag of the country of origin, postal seals and stamps.

The sender can write a short text (200 characters) which will be displayed on the NFT postcard.

Open <a href="https://pcards.near.page" target="_blank">pcards.near.page</a>, log in and fill out the form to send a postcard.

After successful sending, you will be redirected to the page with postcards of the receiver.

<img src="https://telegra.ph/file/1dee2c369f02a4a6761c3.png" />

### Video
https://youtu.be/jYkiEB18GeY

### Build
```
$ cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release
$ copy target\wasm32-unknown-unknown\release\near_postcards.wasm main.wasm 
```
### Deploy
```
$ near deploy --wasmFile main.wasm --accountId account.near
```

### Support
<a href="https://t.me/nearwatch">Near.Watch technical support group (telegram)</a>

'''

'''--- index.html ---
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=720, initial-scale=0.54">
    <title>Near Postcards</title>
    <style>
        * { font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; }
        a, a:link, a:visited, a:focus, a:hover, a:active { outline: none; text-decoration: none; padding: 2px 1px 0; color: #fff;}
        body { padding: 0px; margin: 0px; }
		    .show_card {float:left; width:327px; height:500px; margin-left:20px; margin-bottom:20px; }
		    input:invalid:required {background-image: linear-gradient(to right, pink,#E0F0F0);}
		    input:invalid {background-image: linear-gradient(to right, pink,#E0F0F0);}
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div style='padding:10px; background-color:#89a9a9; color: white;'>
        <img width="25" height="25" style="vertical-align:bottom; padding-right:5px;" src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,">
		<a href="/"><b>Near Postcards</b></a>
		<span id='logged_in_controls' style='display:none'>&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;<a style='color:yellow' href='/'>Send</a>&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;<a style='color:yellow' href="https://github.com/nearwatch/postcards/" target="_blank">Source</a>
		<span style='float: right; display: none' id='logged_in'><span id=whoami></span> <a style='color:yellow' href='#' onclick='logout()'>Log out</a></span>
		</span>
	</div><br>
	<div id='login' style='padding:10px'><button style='background-color:#E0F0F0; height:30px;' onclick='login()'>Login with NEAR</button><br><br></div>
	<div id='cards' style='display:none; padding:10px'>
		<div id='info' style='margin-bottom:20px; padding-left:30px;'><h2>loading ...</h2></div>
		<div id='card0' class='show_card' style='display:none;'></div>
		<div id='card1' class='show_card' style='display:none;'></div>
		<div id='card2' class='show_card' style='display:none;'></div>
		<div id='card3' class='show_card' style='display:none;'></div>
	</div>
	<div id='send' style='display:none;'>
		<div class='show_card' style='height:330px;'>
			<label style="color:#a0a0a0;">greetings from</label>
			<select id='places' size="1" name="places[]" style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px; color:#000000; border:0px; background-color:#E3F1F6; height:30px; width:100%; outline: none; font-size:18px;"></select>
			<label style="color:#a0a0a0;">message</label>
			<textarea id="mess" rows="8" cols="30" autocomplete="off" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" spellcheck="false" maxlength="207" style="color:#000000; border:0px; background-color:#E3F1F6; height:160px; width:100%; outline: none; font-size:16px;margin-bottom:10px; "></textarea>
			<label style="color:#a0a0a0; height:30px; display: flex; align-items: center;">to&nbsp;&nbsp;
				<input id="receiver" value="" required autocomplete="off" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off" spellcheck="false" tabindex="1" maxlength="64" style="float:right; width:100%; color:#000000; border:0px; background-color:#E3F1F6; height:30px; outline: none; font-size:18px;">
			</label>
			<button onclick="sendCard()" style="margin-top:10px; background-color:#E0F0F0; width:100%; height:30px;">Send</button>			
		</div>
		<div id='preview' class='show_card' style="background-color:pink;"></div>
	</div>
	<br />

<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/near-api-js@0.44.0/dist/near-api-js.js"></script>
<script>
	const previewTemplate = '';
	const colors = ["AntiqueWhite","MistyRose","Moccasin","PeachPuff","PaleGoldenrod","Lavender","Thistle","Plum","MediumAquamarine","DarkSeaGreen","LightCyan","PaleTurquoise","PowderBlue","Cornsilk","Tan","SandyBrown","Azure","Beige",];
	const countries = ["Africa","Antarctica","Asia","Australia","Europe","North America","South America","Argentina","Austria","Belarus","Belgium","Brazil","Bulgaria","Canada","China","Cuba","Cyprus","Czechia","Denmark","Egypt","Estonia",
	"Finland","France","Georgia","Germany","Greece","India","Indonesia","Ireland","Israel","Italy","Japan","Kazakhstan","South Korea","Latvia","Lithuania","Malaysia","Mexico","Netherlands","New Zealand","Norway","Philippines",
	"Poland","Portugal","Russia","Saudi Arabia","Singapore","Slovakia","Slovenia","Spain","Sweden","Switzerland","Taiwan","Thailand","Turkey","Ukraine","United Kingdom","United States","Vietnam",];
	const addressValid = (address) => /^([a-z0-9][a-z0-9\.\-\_]+?\.(near))$/i.exec(address);
	const receiver  = document.getElementById("receiver");
	const select = document.getElementById("places");		
    countries.forEach((p,i) => select.append(new Option(p,i+1)));
	select.addEventListener("change",e => update_preview(e.target.selectedIndex));
	mess.addEventListener("input", e => update_preview(null));
	receiver.addEventListener("input", e => receiver.setCustomValidity(addressValid(receiver.value)?'':'Wrong receiver account id'));

	const appName = "Near Postcards";
	const contractName = "pcards.near";
	window.nearConfig = {networkId:'mainnet', nodeUrl:'https://rpc.mainnet.near.org', contractName: contractName, walletUrl: 'https://wallet.near.org', helperUrl: 'https://helper.mainnet.near.org'};
	window.nearInitPromise = connect().then(() => {
		const wallet = window.location.pathname && window.location.pathname.substr(1).toLowerCase();
		const sendArea  = document.getElementById('send');
		if (addressValid(wallet)){
			sendArea.style.display = 'none';
			const cardsArea = document.getElementById('cards');
			const infoArea  = document.getElementById('info');
			cardsArea.style.display = '';
			window.contract.account.viewFunction(contractName,'nft_tokens_for_owner',{account_id:wallet,from_index:'0',limit:4})
			.then(data => {
				info.innerHTML = '<h1>'+wallet+'</h1>';
				if (data && data.length){
					for (let i=0;i<data.length;i++){
						if (data[i] && data[i].metadata && data[i].metadata.media){
							const cardImage = document.getElementById('card'+i);
							cardImage.style.display = '';
							try{
								cardImage.innerHTML = '<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,'+Buffer.from(decodeURIComponent(data[i].metadata.media.substr(19))).toString('base64')+'" />';
							}catch(err){console.log(err);}	
						}
					}
				} else info.innerHTML = '<div><h3>No postcards found for '+wallet+'</h3></div>';
			}).catch(err => {console.log(err)})
		}
	}).catch(console.error);

	function update_preview(from){
		if (from === null){
			const select = document.getElementById("places");		
			from = select.selectedIndex
		}
		const mess = document.getElementById("mess");		
		text = (mess.value.trim()+'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n').split('\n')
		const previewArea = document.getElementById('preview');
		let template = 'data:image/svg+xml,'+Buffer.from(previewTemplate,'base64').toString().replace('{}',colors[from%18]).replace('{}','data:image/svg+xml;base64,====').replace('{}',new Date().toISOString().substr(0,10)).replace('{}',countries[from%59]);
		for (const line of text) template = template.replace('{}',line);
		previewArea.innerHTML = '<img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64,'+Buffer.from(decodeURIComponent(template.substr(19))).toString('base64')+'" />';
	}
	async function sendCard(){	
		if (!addressValid(receiver.value)) return receiver.focus(); 
		const params = {receiver_id:receiver.value, country:select.selectedIndex, text:mess.value.replace(/\n/g,'\r\n')};
        window.contract.account._signAndSendTransaction({receiverId:contractName, actions:[nearApi.transactions.functionCall('nft_mint', params, 100000000000000, '10000000000000000000000')],walletCallbackUrl:'https://pcards.near.page/'+receiver.value});
	}
	function login() {
		walletAccount.requestSignIn(contractName, appName);
	}
	function logout() {
		walletAccount.signOut();
		window.location.replace(window.location.origin + window.location.pathname);
	}
	async function connect(){
		window.near = await nearApi.connect(Object.assign(nearConfig, { deps: { keyStore: new nearApi.keyStores.BrowserLocalStorageKeyStore() }}));
		window.walletAccount = new nearApi.WalletConnection(window.near);
		window.accountId = walletAccount.getAccountId();
		window.contract = await new nearApi.Contract(walletAccount.account(), nearConfig.contractName, {viewMethods:['nft_tokens_for_owner'], changeMethods:['nft_mint'], sender: window.walletAccount.getAccountId()});
		if (walletAccount.isSignedIn()) {
			document.getElementById('login').style.display = 'none';
			document.getElementById('logged_in_controls').style.display = '';
			document.getElementById('send').style.display = '';
			document.getElementById('logged_in').style.display = '';
			document.getElementById('whoami').innerText = walletAccount.getAccountId();
			update_preview(null);
		}
	}
</script>
</body>
</html>

'''--- lib.rs ---
use near_sdk::borsh::{self, BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize};
use near_sdk::serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use near_sdk::json_types::{U128,Base64VecU8};
use near_sdk::{env, require, near_bindgen};
use near_sdk::collections::{LookupMap};
use chrono::prelude::DateTime;
use chrono::Utc;
use std::time::{UNIX_EPOCH, Duration};

const DATA_IMAGE_SVG_NEAR_ICON: &str = "data:image/svg+xml;base64,";
macro_rules! POSTCARD_TEMPLATE {() => {include_str!("card.svg")}}

#[near_bindgen]
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize)]
pub struct Contract {
	accounts: LookupMap<String, Vec<CardData>>,
}
impl Default for Contract {
	fn default() -> Self {
		Self {
			accounts: LookupMap::new(b"a".to_vec()), 
		}
	}
}
#[allow(non_snake_case)]
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct Web4Request {
    accountId: Option<String>,
    path: String,
}
#[allow(non_snake_case)]
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct Web4Response {
    contentType: String,
    body: Vec<u8>,
    preloadUrls: Vec<String>,
}
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Deserialize, Serialize)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct NFTContractMetadata {
    pub spec: String,              
    pub name: String,              
    pub symbol: String,            
    pub icon: Option<String>,      
    pub base_uri: Option<String>,  
    pub reference: Option<String>, 
    pub reference_hash: Option<Base64VecU8>,
}
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Serialize, Clone)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct TokenMetadata {
    pub title: Option<String>, 
    pub media: Option<String>, 
}
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Serialize, Clone)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct Token {
    pub receiver_id: String,
    pub metadata: Option<TokenMetadata>,
}
#[derive(BorshDeserialize, BorshSerialize, Serialize, Clone)]
#[serde(crate = "near_sdk::serde")]
pub struct CardData {
    pub from: u8,     
	pub date: String, 
    pub text: String, 
}
#[near_bindgen]
impl Contract {
    pub fn web4_get(&self) -> Web4Response {
        let (content_type, body) = ("text/html",include_bytes!("index.html").to_vec());
        Web4Response {contentType:content_type.to_string(), body, preloadUrls: vec![]}
    }
    pub fn nft_metadata(&self) -> NFTContractMetadata {
        NFTContractMetadata {
            spec: "nft-1.0.0".to_string(),
            name: "Near Postcards".to_string(),
            symbol: "NPC".to_string(),
            icon: Some(DATA_IMAGE_SVG_NEAR_ICON.to_string()),
            base_uri: None,
            reference: None,
            reference_hash: None,
        }
    }
    fn get_card(&self, receiver_id:String, card:CardData) -> Token {
		let ptr1:usize = card.from as usize % 59;
		let ptr2:usize = card.from as usize % 18;
		let mut lines = card.text.lines();
		let metadata = TokenMetadata {title:None, media:Some(format!(POSTCARD_TEMPLATE!(),BCLR[ptr2],FLAGS[ptr1],card.date,COUNTRIES[ptr1],
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			match lines.next() {None => "", Some(t) => t},
			receiver_id
		))};
        Token {receiver_id:receiver_id.clone(), metadata:Some(metadata)} 
    }
    pub fn nft_tokens(&self) -> Vec<Token> {vec![]}
    pub fn nft_tokens_for_owner(&self, account_id:String, from_index:Option<U128>, limit:usize) -> Vec<Token> {
        let start_index: u128 = from_index.map(From::from).unwrap_or_default();
		let mut list = match self.accounts.get(&account_id){
			Some(cards) => cards,
			None => vec![],
		};
        require!(start_index <= list.len() as u128,"Out of bounds, please use a smaller from_index.");
		list = list.split_off(start_index as usize);
		if  limit <= list.len() {
			list.split_off(limit);
		}
        match self.accounts.contains_key(&account_id) {
            true  => list.into_iter().map(|card| self.get_card(account_id.clone(),card.clone())).rev().collect(),
            false => vec![]
        }
    }
	pub fn nft_total_supply(&self) -> u8 { 0 }
	pub fn nft_supply_for_owner(&self, account_id: String) -> usize {
        match self.accounts.contains_key(&account_id) {
			true => match self.accounts.get(&account_id){
						Some(cards) => cards.len(),
						None => 0,
					}, 
			false => 0
		}
    }
	#[payable]
    pub fn nft_mint(&mut self, receiver_id:String, country:u8, text:String) {  // -> Token
		require!(env::attached_deposit() >= 10_000_000_000_000_000_000_000,"Not enough deposit for buying the account");
		let mut list = match self.accounts.get(&receiver_id){
			Some(cards) => cards,
			None => vec![],
		};
		let timestamp:&str = &env::block_timestamp().to_string()[..10];
		let d = UNIX_EPOCH + Duration::from_secs(timestamp.parse::<u64>().unwrap());
		let date = DateTime::<Utc>::from(d);

		list.push(CardData {from:country, date:date.format("%d.%m.%Y").to_string(), text:text.chars().take(230).collect()});
		if list.len()>4 {
			list = list.split_off(1);
		};
        self.accounts.insert(&(receiver_id.clone()),&(list)); 
        env::log_str(&format!("Postcard send to {}", receiver_id));
    }
}
